The paper deals with graph and digraph classes that are generalizations of interval graphs, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses ordering characterizations and recognition algorithms, which are topics that are often studied in the areas of graph theory (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes a new class of digraphs called signed-interval digraphs, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
